B.u3=s(["All Themes","Tropical Getaways","Mountain Expeditions","Cultural Heritage","Adventure Sports"],t.s)
B.UK=s(["Kyoto's most celebrated temples are undeniably magnificent. Yet they share their beauty with thousands of visitors daily. The true magic of this ancient capital lies in the spaces between the crowds.","Begin your exploration in the Higashiyama district at dawn, when the stone-paved lanes of Ninenzaka and Sannenzaka are still mist-wrapped and quiet. The vermillion pagoda of Yasaka Koshindo, adorned with hundreds of colorful temari balls, rewards early risers with solitude and soft morning light.","Further north, the Fushimi Ward hides Daigo-ji \u2014 a UNESCO World Heritage Site with a five-story pagoda that predates most of Kyoto's famous landmarks. Its Sambo-in garden represents the pinnacle of Momoyama-period garden design.","For the most contemplative experience, seek out Jizo-in in Nishikyo Ward \u2014 a small Zen temple where novice monks practice raking patterns into a sea of moss beneath a canopy of ancient maple trees. Autumn transforms this garden into a cathedral of crimson and amber light.","Practical tip: Download the Kyoto City Bus app and invest in a one-day bus pass. Many hidden temples are connected by the city's extensive bus network, making an independent temple-hopping itinerary both affordable and flexible."],t.s)
B.UC=s(["Kyoto","Japan","Temples","Culture","Hidden Gems"],t.s)
B.Gu=new A.i7("1","The Hidden Temples of Kyoto: A Traveler's Complete Guide","Venture beyond the tourist trail and discover ancient sanctuaries tucked away in bamboo forests and quiet hillside neighborhoods that most visitors never find.",B.UK,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1545569341-9eb8b30979d9?w=1200","Theme","Sarah Chen","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494790108377-be9c29b29330?w=200","Sarah has been traveling Asia for over a decade, specializing in cultural heritage sites and off-the-beaten-path experiences. Based in Singapore.","Mar 12, 2026",8,B.UC,!0)
B.V9=s(["The train from Kandy to Ella is routinely listed among the world's most scenic rail journeys. As the locomotive hauls its carriages up through cascading waterfalls and silver-hued mist, the air cools and the landscape transforms into rolling seas of manicured tea.","Nuwara Eliya, at 1,868 meters above sea level, carries the architectural memory of British colonial ambitions. The Hill Club, established in 1876, still enforces a jacket-and-tie dinner rule in its paneled dining room.","The real draw is the tea itself. Arrange a factory visit at Mackwoods Labookellie Estate, where the entire process from withering leaf to finished Orthodox tea can be followed in under an hour.","Ella has a more youthful energy. The hike to Little Adam's Peak at dawn offers a panorama of valleys so vast that distance becomes abstract. Return via the Nine Arch Bridge \u2014 a colonial-era viaduct carved from solid stone that appears to grow organically from the tea-blanketed hillside."],t.s)
B.Wt=s(["Sri Lanka","Tea","Highlands","Train","Nature"],t.s)
B.Gx=new A.i7("2","Sri Lanka's Tea Country: A Journey Through Misty Highlands","From colonial Nuwara Eliya to the emerald terraces above Ella, Sri Lanka's hill country rewards slow travelers with some of Asia's most dramatic landscapes.",B.V9,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1586375300773-8384e3e4916f?w=1200","Country","James Walker","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472099645785-5658abf4ff4e?w=200","James is an adventure travel writer and photographer with a focus on South and Southeast Asia. His work has appeared in Cond\xe9 Nast Traveler.","Mar 5, 2026",7,B.Wt,!1)
B.UJ=s(["Jemaa el-Fna transforms as the day lengthens. Morning brings orange juice vendors and storytellers; by evening, it has become the world's largest open-air restaurant, with dozens of competing stalls trailing plumes of charcoal smoke into the indigo sky.","Begin with a bowl of harira \u2014 the velvety tomato, lentil, and lamb soup traditionally used to break the Ramadan fast. A 10-dirham cup from a cart near the Koutoubia Mosque is as authentic as the dish gets.","The pastilla \u2014 a phyllo pastry parcel stuffed with pigeon, almonds, and cinnamon, dusted with powdered sugar \u2014 represents the apex of Moroccan cuisine's sweet-savory complexity.","Don't miss the snail soup sellers who set up near the Djemaa post-sunset. A small bowl of garden snails, simmered in a broth of thyme and licorice root, costs around 5 dirhams and is arguably the most unique flavour the city offers.","For something sweet, seek out chebakia \u2014 sesame-seed cookies fried in argan oil, dipped in honey \u2014 at the confectionery stalls in the Mellah market."],t.s)
B.VG=s(["Morocco","Marrakech","Food","Street Food","Culture"],t.s)
B.Gz=new A.i7("3","Moroccan Street Food: 15 Must-Try Dishes in Marrakech","The ancient medina of Marrakech is one of the world's great street food destinations. Navigate its labyrinthine lanes with confidence using this essential culinary guide.",B.UJ,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1539020140153-e479b8d978a7?w=1200","Country","Amira Osei","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531746020798-e6953c6e8e04?w=200",'Amira is a food writer and culinary travel specialist. She has documented street food cultures across 40+ countries and hosts the podcast "Eaten Alive."',"Feb 28, 2026",9,B.VG,!1)
B.Wx=s(["Southeast Asia receives over 130 million international tourists annually. The environmental pressure on fragile reef ecosystems is significant \u2014 but so is the positive economic impact of thoughtful, well-directed tourism spending.","The first principle of sustainable travel is slow travel. Spending two weeks in one country rather than island-hopping across five dramatically reduces your carbon footprint and keeps more money circulating in local communities.","Choose accommodation that is locally owned and demonstrates genuine environmental stewardship: composting, solar power, local staff. Certification schemes like Green Globe provide a useful starting point.","Reef protection is critical in the Coral Triangle. Reef-safe sunscreen \u2014 free from oxybenzone and octinoxate \u2014 is non-negotiable when snorkelling or diving. Never touch coral, never take shells.","Support the local economy directly: eat at family-run warungs, hire local guides, and buy crafts directly from artisans. The difference in income retained locally is substantial."],t.s)
B.Ul=s(["Sustainability","Southeast Asia","Eco Travel","Tips"],t.s)
B.Gt=new A.i7("4","How to Travel Sustainably in Southeast Asia","Practical, actionable advice for reducing your environmental footprint without sacrificing the depth or quality of your travel experience across the region.",B.Wx,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?w=1200","Theme","Lena Park","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1438761681033-6461ffad8d80?w=200","Lena is a sustainability consultant and travel writer. She advises tourism businesses on environmental certification and runs workshops for frequent travelers.","Feb 20, 2026",10,B.Ul,!1)
B.WH=s(["The windows of opportunity for Northern Lights viewing run from late September to early April, with December through February offering the longest nights and the most viewing hours.","Budget accommodation has improved dramatically. The network of guesthouses operated by Icelandic Farm Holidays offers authentic rural stays at roughly half the price of Reykjavik hotels.","The Northern Lights are entirely free to watch once you're outside the capital's light pollution. The Reykjanes Peninsula, accessible by bus from Reykjavik, offers dark skies and geothermal activity in the same landscape.","Self-catering reduces food costs significantly. A weekly shop at B\xf3nus supermarket costs a fraction of restaurant prices. Save restaurant spending for one or two memorable meals.","App recommendation: The Icelandic Met Office's Ve\xf0ur app provides real-time cloud cover maps. Paired with the Aurora Forecast app, it makes self-guided aurora hunting genuinely practical."],t.s)
B.UW=s(["Iceland","Northern Lights","Budget Travel","Winter"],t.s)
B.Gy=new A.i7("5","Iceland in Winter: Chasing Northern Lights on a Budget","Iceland's reputation as an expensive destination is warranted \u2014 but with careful planning, a winter trip to see the aurora borealis is more achievable than you think.",B.WH,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531168556467-80aace0d0144?w=1200","Month","Marco Silva","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500648767791-00dcc994a43e?w=200","Marco is a budget travel specialist who has visited 80 countries. He writes about making transformative travel accessible to everyone.","Feb 14, 2026",11,B.UW,!1)
B.Wh=s(["Pura Tirta Empul, nestled in a shaded valley near Ubud, is Bali's most sacred water temple. Fed by a natural spring said to have been created by the god Indra, its bathing pools have drawn Hindu pilgrims for over a thousand years.","The Subak system \u2014 connecting over 1,200 water temples, irrigation channels, and rice paddies \u2014 was inscribed as a UNESCO Cultural Landscape in 2012. It represents a working model of ecological spirituality.","Pura Ulun Danu Batur, perched on the caldera rim of Mount Batur, manages water distribution for the entire eastern agricultural region. The views across the volcanic lake are extraordinary.","The Tirta Gangga water palace in East Bali combines royal ambition with spiritual function: tiered fountains, koi-filled pools, and stepping stone paths spread across a landscape garden commissioned by the last Raja of Karangasem in 1948."],t.s)
B.WJ=s(["Bali","Indonesia","Temples","Culture","Spirituality"],t.s)
B.Gw=new A.i7("6","Bali's Sacred Water Temples: Where Spirituality Meets Nature","The Subak irrigation system that sustains Bali's emerald rice terraces is managed by a network of water temples whose ceremonies have governed the island's agricultural calendar for centuries.",B.Wh,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1537996194471-e657df975ab4?w=1200","Country","Priya Nair","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1489424731084-a5d8b219a5bb?w=200","Priya is a cultural anthropologist and travel writer focused on Hindu sacred landscapes across Asia. She has lived in Bali for three years.","Feb 8, 2026",7,B.WJ,!1)
B.V_=s(["The Swiss Alps contain some of the world's most accessible high-mountain terrain. An extensive network of cable cars means adventure activities can be combined with surprisingly comfortable logistics.","Via ferrata \u2014 iron-route climbing using fixed cables, rungs, and ladders \u2014 is the ideal entry point for those with limited technical climbing experience. Routes above M\xfcrren range from Grade B (beginner) to Grade D/E (expert).","Paragliding from Interlaken's First mountain station has been offered commercially for over 30 years, making it one of Europe's most practiced tandem operations.","Canyon Sauvage in the Haslital valley offers canyoneering for beginners: wetsuits provided, with natural water slides, cliff jumps, and gorge swims through turquoise plunge pools. The guide-to-guest ratio is strictly maintained."],t.s)
B.WE=s(["Alps","Switzerland","Adventure","Via Ferrata","Paragliding"],t.s)
B.Gv=new A.i7("7","Adventure Sports in the Swiss Alps: A Beginner's Guide","The Alps offer an extraordinary range of adventure experiences for every fitness level \u2014 from gentle via ferrata routes to high-alpine ski touring and world-class paragliding.",B.V_,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1464822759023-fed622ff2c3b?w=1200","Theme","Tom Brennan","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519085360753-af0119f7cbe7?w=200","Tom is a former professional mountaineer and outdoor sports journalist. He holds IFMGA mountain guide certification and has guided expeditions on six continents.","Jan 30, 2026",12,B.WE,!1)
B.Wb=s(["The mathematics of conventional travel is seductive: more countries, more stamps, more photographs. But this arithmetic produces a particular kind of traveler \u2014 one who has seen a great deal and understood very little.","The inflection point comes when a traveler stays somewhere long enough for the unfamiliar to become normal. When you know which bakery opens earliest, when the owner saves your preferred table \u2014 that is when travel yields its deepest returns.","Practically, slow travel means renting an apartment rather than booking hotel rooms, shopping at local markets, and learning enough of the language to navigate daily life without assistance.","The cost implications are frequently counterintuitive. Monthly apartment rentals in Lisbon, Chiang Mai, Tbilisi, or Mexico City often work out cheaper per night than budget hotels, with self-catering dramatically reducing food costs.","The environmental case is equally compelling. A month in one destination produces a fraction of the transport emissions generated by the same calendar time spent moving between ten destinations."],t.s)
B.TM=s(["Slow Travel","Digital Nomad","Budget","Sustainability"],t.s)
B.Gs=new A.i7("8","The Art of Slow Travel: Why Less Places Changes Everything","In a world that celebrates the longest passport stamp collections, there is a growing movement of travelers choosing depth over breadth \u2014 and they're coming back profoundly changed.",B.Wb,"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1503220317375-aaad61436b1b?w=1200","Duration","Yuki Tanaka","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506794778202-cad84cf45f1d?w=200","Yuki is a writer and digital nomad who has spent five years practicing slow travel across Europe, Asia, and Latin America.","Jan 22, 2026",9,B.TM,!1)
B.em=s([B.Gu,B.Gx,B.Gz,B.Gt,B.Gy,B.Gw,B.Gv,B.Gs],A.al("I<i7>"))
